<subSubSection pageId="148" pageNumber="546" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="148.[1446,2661,1437,2100]" pageId="148" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1452,1808,1910,1943]" pageId="148" pageNumber="546">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The [UCN Red List. Meester’s Mouse Shrew was only recently described as a distinct species. It does not appear to be under major threat, as it has a relatively wide distribution, and is found in Gorongosa National Park.
</paragraph>
